		"title": "USN-4348-1 -- Mailman vulnerabilities",
		"description": "It was discovered that Mailman incorrectly handled certain inputs. An attacker could possibly use this to issue execute arbitrary scripts or HTML. (CVE-2018-0618)  It was discovered that Mailman incorrectly handled certain inputs. An attacker could possibly use this issue to display arbitrary text on a web page. (CVE-2018-13796)  It was discovered that Mailman incorrectly handled certain files. An attacker could possibly use this issue to execute arbitrary code. (CVE-2020-12137)  Update Instructions:  Run `sudo pro fix USN-4348-1` to fix the vulnerability. The problem can be corrected by updating your system to the following package versions:  mailman - 1:2.1.26-1ubuntu0.1 No subscription required",
